{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Make your custom types easier to use by ensuring that they conform to Swift protocols."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using custom types to model data in your programs, you may frequently need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"check whether two values are the same or different, or whether a particular value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is included in a list of values. This capability, as well as the ability to store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values in a set or use them as keys in a dictionary, are governed by two related"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"standard library protocols, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can compare instances of an "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"equatable","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" type by using the equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":") and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not-equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"!="},{"text":") operators.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An instance of a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hashable"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" type can reduce its value mathematically to a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"integer, which is used internally by sets and dictionaries to make lookups consistently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fast.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Many standard library types are both equatable and hashable, including strings, integers,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"floating-point values, Boolean values, and collections of equatable and hashable","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types. The "},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" comparison and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"contains(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method call in the following example","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"depend on strings and integers being equatable:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["if username == \"Arturo\" {","    print(\"Hi, Arturo!\")","}","","let favoriteNumbers = [4, 7, 8, 9]","if favoriteNumbers.contains(todaysDate.day) {","    print(\"It's a good day today!\")","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforming to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocols is straightforward and makes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it easier to use your own types in Swift. It’s a good idea for all your custom model"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types to conform."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Conform Automatically to Equatable and Hashable","anchor":"Conform-Automatically-to-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can make many custom types equatable and hashable by simply declaring these protocol","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conformances in the same file as the type’s original declaration. Add ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" to the list of adopted protocols when declaring the type, and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compiler automatically fills in the requirements for the two protocols:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/\/ A position in an x-y coordinate system.","struct Position: Equatable, Hashable {","    var x: Int","    var y: Int","","    init(_ x: Int, _ y: Int) {","        self.x = x","        self.y = y","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance, you can use the equal-to operator ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":") or the not-equal-to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operator ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"!="},{"type":"text","text":") with any two instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Position"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let availablePositions = [Position(0, 0), Position(0, 1), Position(1, 0)]","let gemPosition = Position(1, 0)","","for position in availablePositions {","    if gemPosition == position {","        print(\"Gem found at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))!\")","    } else {","        print(\"No gem at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))\")","    }","}","\/\/ No gem at (0, 0)","\/\/ No gem at (0, 1)","\/\/ Gem found at (1, 0)!",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance means that you can store positions in a set and quickly check"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether you’ve visited a position before, as shown in the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var visitedPositions: Set = [Position(0, 0), Position(1, 0)]","let currentPosition = Position(1, 3)","","if visitedPositions.contains(currentPosition) {","    print(\"Already visited (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","} else {","    print(\"First time at (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","    visitedPositions.insert(currentPosition)","}","\/\/ First time at (1, 3)",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition to simplifying your code, this automatic conformance reduces errors,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because any new properties you add to your custom types are automatically included"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when hashing and testing for equality. A type is eligible for automatic conformance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" when it’s a structure or an enumeration that meets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these criteria:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a structure, "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"type":"text","text":" its stored properties must conform to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an enumeration, "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" its associated values must conform to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":". (Enumerations without associated values have "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformance even without declaring adoption.)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Conform Manually to Equatable and Hashable","anchor":"Conform-Manually-to-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to manually implement "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance for a type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in these cases:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type doesn’t meet the criteria listed in the previous section."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to customize the type’s conformance."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to extend a type declared in another file or module to conform."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class Player {","    var name: String","    var position: Position","","    init(name: String, position: Position) {","        self.name = name","        self.position = position","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"text":" type is a class, so it doesn’t qualify for automatic synthesis of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" requirements. To make this class conform to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"protocol, declare conformance in an extension and implement the  static ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. Compare each significant property for equality in your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method’s implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension Player: Equatable {","    static func ==(lhs: Player, rhs: Player) -> Bool {","        return lhs.name == rhs.name && lhs.position == rhs.position","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To make ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"type":"text","text":" conform to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, declare conformance in another"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extension and implement the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. In the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method, call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combine(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method on the provided hasher with each significant property:"}]},{"code":["extension Player: Hashable {","    func hash(into hasher: inout Hasher) {","        hasher.combine(name)","        hasher.combine(position)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Use All Significant Properties for Equatable and Hashable","anchor":"Use-All-Significant-Properties-for-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When implementing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"hash(into:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method, use all the properties","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that affect whether two instances of your custom type are considered equal. In the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementations above, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Player","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"position"},{"text":" in both methods.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your type contains properties that don’t affect whether two instances are considered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"equal, exclude those properties from comparison in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method and from hashing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":". For example, a type might cache an expensive computed value so","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it only needs to calculate it once. If you compare two instances of that type,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether or not the computed value has been cached shouldn’t affect their equality,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so the cached value should be excluded from comparison and hashing.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always use the same properties in both your "},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"hash(into:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" methods."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Using different groups of properties in the two methods can lead to unexpected behavior"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or performance when using your custom type in sets and dictionaries.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"important"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/adopting-common-protocols","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Adopting Common Protocols"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Data-Modeling","title":"Data Modeling","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes"],"generated":true}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/choosing-between-structures-and-classes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Decide how to store data and model behavior.","type":"text"}],"title":"Choosing Between Structures and Classes","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Hashable":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Hashable","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/hashable","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Hashable","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable","title":"Hashable","abstract":[{"text":"A type that can be hashed into a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hasher","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to produce an integer hash value.","type":"text"}]},"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["2x","light"],"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png"},{"traits":["2x","dark"],"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background."},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Equatable":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/equatable","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Equatable","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A type that can be compared for value equality.","type":"text"}],"title":"Equatable","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Equatable","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"}}}